==Old English==
===Etymology===
Common to West and North Germanic: cognate with Old Norse [[kǫttr]] (Swedish [[katt]]), Old High German [[kazza]].  The word existed in the Germanic languages in a female gender also, represented in OE by [[catte]].  The word appears to be related to late Latin [[cattus]] as well as to similar words in the Slavic and Celtic languages, but the ultimate source is uncertain.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'katt/

